app idea: clubhouse-tiktok-youtube hybrid. the idea is like youtube  the recorded audio can be of unrestricted length  but it's organised in a manner similar to tiktok's layout. With podcasts you have to search and find podcasts actively. Producing podcasts is also quite involved. The idea with this app's recorded portion is you just pick up your phone  talk  maybe edit a little  then upload. The emphasis here is on discovery and interesting convos and people. Most podcast apps are set up such that you have to actively search out new podcasts  and even with reccomended podcasts  you normally just press play and listen to the same podcast either until you're up to the latest episode or you pause the podcast player. With this  it's more of an endless radio station with a variety of content curated in a feed format. For the live portion  it's live audio streams or chatrooms that can be recorded then put up on the recorded portion for posterity. What do you think?
